In 2015, the Sohu Group recognized tax payable in the amount of $14.6 million as management determined that certain business transactions that took place during the year may result in additional tax obligations under relevant tax rules. In 2013, the Sohu Group recognized a tax payable amount of $21.4 million for an uncertain tax position arising from certain equity transactions that may be considered by PRC tax authorities to have resulted in taxable income. The $3.1 million balance brought forward from previous years was related to an uncertain tax position generated in 2009.

The Group does not anticipate that the uncertain tax positions will significantly increase or decrease within twelve months of December 31, 2015.

